data.description: A single dwelling unit usually inhabited by one family.
A general tag for a building used primarily for residential purposes.
Denotes a single-owner private garage
A building arranged into individual dwellings, often on separate floors. May also have retail outlets on the ground floor.
A small and crude shelter.
A building where some industrial process takes place.
A roof open on at least two sides.
A block of private garages each with a separate owner
A free-standing residential building usually housing a single-family.
A building where non-specific commercial activities take place.

A single way used to define the outline of a linear row of residential dwellings, each of which normally has its own entrance, which form a terrace ("row-house" or "townhouse" in North American English).
A small, simple structure used as storage or workshop
A generic school building.
A building primarily used for selling goods to the general public.
A building on a farm that is not a dwelling.
A building that was built as a church.
A building in which plants are grown
An agricultural building used for storage and as a covered workplace.
A building under construction
Service building usually is a small umanned building with certain machinery (like pumps or transformers).
A residential building on a farm (farmhouse).
A small, roughly built house typically found in rural areas.
A commercial building for storage of goods.
To mark the location of a building entrance.
A building hosting any civic amenity (town hall, library, swimming pool).
A hangar is a building used for the storage of airplanes, helicopters or space-craft.
A building accessible to general public (town hall, police station, court house).
An university building.
A building which forms part of a hospital.
A mobile home (caravan) (semi)permanently left on a single site.
A train station building
A boat used primarily as a home.
College or university dormitory for shared living of its students.
A generic kindergarten building.
A building or part of a building that is used as a stable for horses
A hardened military building.
